 is Time Complexity?</h2>\n            <p>Time complexity is a measure of how long an algorithm takes to complete, usually expressed as a function of the input size.</p>\n            <h2>Big O Notation</h2>\n            <p>Big O notation is a way to describe the time complexity of an algorithm using a mathematical formula. There are several types of Big O notation, including:</p>\n            <ul>\n                <li>O(1)</li>\n                <li>O(log n)</li>\n                <li>O(n)</li>\n                <li>O(n log n)</li>\n                <li>O(2^n)</li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"button-container\">\n            <button class=\"button\" onclick=\"showTimeComplexity()\">Learn More</button>\n            <button class=\"button\" onclick=\"showTimeComplexity()\">Understand Big O Notation</button>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        function showTimeComplexity() {\n            const content = document.querySelector('.content');\n            content.style.display = content.style.display === 'block' ? 'none' : 'block';\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
